cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CE, cs.ETM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on control of distributed energy resources in residential distribution feeders through power flow analysis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for joint estimation of model parameters and operational structure of a distribution network using telemetry data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper develops an online algorithm for early detection and localization of critical events in the distribution network. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses power flow studies on real distribution systems to validate the proposed techniques. 
- cs.ETM (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the recent introduction of synchrophasor technology in low-voltage distribution grids and its potential for learning the distribution system model.
